beer.beer_description: So you want a beer for summer, fresh and light, to drink it all in one tasty sip, and have it actually taste good? Well, here it is! "Stelle e Strisce" - meaning 'Stars and Stripes' - is a refreshing but surprisingly intense Golden Ale, with a lighter shade of gold and an unusually low alcohol content. We dedicated it to 'Old Glory' because we use an interesting cocktail of American hops, most of them added in dry hopping. In this process, fresh hops are inserted directly into the fermentation process. This gives the brew exceptional freshness, intense hoppy aromas, and flavors of herbs and citrus throughout. All contribute to a crisp, light, and refreshing beer in the mouth at surprisingly low 3.5% ABV. The finish is perfectly balanced with notes of pleasant bitterness. An all around great beer, perfect for the warm months, reminding one of sandy Californian beaches or a summer on the lake.
